Class Timeslot

java.lang.Object
clinic.Timeslot
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<Timeslot>
public class Timeslot extends Object implements Comparable<Timeslot>
Represents a time slot for scheduling appointments with hour and minute fields. Implements Comparable to allow comparison between time slots. This class provides utility methods for formatting and comparing times.
Author:
Joshua Goykhman (Netid: jg1986)

    • getTimeslotInt

      public int getTimeslotInt()
      Converts the hour and minute of this Timeslot into a corresponding integer timeslot value. - If the hour is 13 or greater (1:00 PM or later), the timeslot value starts at 5 and increments by 2 for each hour. - If the hour is between 9 and 12 (morning), the timeslot value starts at 1 and increments by 2 for each hour. - If the minute is 30 or greater, 1 is added to the timeslot value to represent the half-hour slot. - If the hour is less than 9 or greater than 24, the method returns -1 indicating an invalid timeslot.
      Returns:
      The timeslot value representing the hour and minute, or -1 if the time is invalid.
